<h3 class=3D"wp-block-heading fusion-responsive-typography-calculated" data=
-fontsize=3D"30" style=3D"--fontSize: 30; line-height: 1.3;" data-lineheigh=
t=3D"39px" id=3D"toc_3_Understand_the_parallelograms_base_and_height">3. Un=
derstand the parallelogram=E2=80=99s base and height</h3>



<p class=3D"">The base of this new parallelogram is</p>



<p class=3D"has-text-align-center"><strong>New base =3D base=E2=82=81 + bas=
e=E2=82=82</strong></p>



<p class=3D"">, since you combined both parallel sides of the original trap=
ezoid. The height stays the same as the trapezoid=E2=80=99s original height=
.</p>



<p class=3D"has-text-align-center"><strong>Height =3D original height of th=
e trapezoid</strong></p>



<p class=3D""></p>



<h3 class=3D"wp-block-heading fusion-responsive-typography-calculated" data=
-fontsize=3D"30" style=3D"--fontSize: 30; line-height: 1.3;" data-lineheigh=
t=3D"39px" id=3D"toc_4_Use_the_parallelogram_area_formula">4. Use the paral=
lelogram area formula</h3>



<p class=3D"has-text-align-center"><strong>Area of parallelogram =3D (base=
=E2=82=81 + base=E2=82=82) =C3=97 height</strong></p>



<p class=3D""></p>



<h3 class=3D"wp-block-heading fusion-responsive-typography-calculated" data=
-fontsize=3D"30" style=3D"--fontSize: 30; line-height: 1.3;" data-lineheigh=
t=3D"39px" id=3D"toc_5_Find_the_trapezoids_area">5. Find the trapezoid=E2=
=80=99s area</h3>



<p class=3D"">Since the parallelogram is made from two identical trapezoids=
, the area of one trapezoid is half of the parallelogram=E2=80=99s area:</p=
>



<p class=3D"has-text-align-center"><strong>Area of the trapezoid =3D =C2=BD=
 =C3=97 area of the parallelogram =3D =C2=BD =C3=97 (base=E2=82=81 + base=
=E2=82=82) =C3=97 height</strong></p>



<p class=3D"">And that=E2=80=99s the trapezoid area formula!</p>



<p class=3D"has-text-align-center"><strong>Area of trapezoid =3D =C2=BD =C3=
=97 (base=E2=82=81 + base=E2=82=82) =C3=97 height</strong></p>



<p class=3D"">Understanding the formula this way helps you not only remembe=
r it but also trust why it works =E2=80=94 and that makes geometry much eas=
ier and more fun!</p>



<h2 class=3D"wp-block-heading fusion-responsive-typography-calculated" data=
