t=3D"33.6px"><strong>Example 2</strong></h4>



<p class=3D"">A trapezoid has an area of 108 square units, one base of 8 un=
its, and a height of 12 units. What is the length of the other base?</p>



<p class=3D""><strong>Answer:</strong></p>



<p class=3D"">Use the formula&nbsp;<strong>Area of trapezoid =3D =C2=BD =C3=
=97 (base=E2=82=81 + base=E2=82=82) =C3=97 height</strong></p>



<p class=3D"">108 =3D =C2=BD =C3=97 (8 + base=E2=82=82) =C3=97 12</p>



<p class=3D"">108 =3D 6 =C3=97 (8 + base=E2=82=82)</p>



<p class=3D"">18 =3D 8 + base=E2=82=82</p>



<p class=3D"">base=E2=82=82 =3D 10</p>



<p class=3D"">The answer is 10.</p>



